&lt;p&gt;Greenbrook Healthcare - Together, we deliver the future of Urgent Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Greenbrook Healthcare is a wholly owned subsidiary of Totally PLC Totally plc addresses the challenges of increased demand on healthcare services by delivering high-quality planned, urgent and insourcing healthcare across the UK and Ireland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regional Head of Nursing / Regional Lead Practitioner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fixed term contract 6 months-Full time - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary - £61,200 - £66,300 (Inclusive of HCAS) - dependant on experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous flexible benefits including NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location : various Urgent Treatment Centres acrossNorth-West London and West London.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to progress in a definitive career path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to bespoke fully funded training programmes such as apprenticeships &amp; training options, both degree level and bespoke in-house programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to a great support network&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Are you a high impact leader who is ready to lead a team of well-established Emergency Practitioners across a number of UTCs?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to develop your clinical management skills and have the opportunity to progress?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Do you want to help us to deliver an even better service to our patients?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have answered YES to the above, then we want to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an excellent opportunity to join the UK&#39;s leading provider of Urgent Treatment Centres as Head of Nursing across our services in North and West London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&#39;s an exciting time for Greenbrook Healthcare, following many years of sustained growth and plans to expand further, we require a Regional Lead Emergency Practitionerto bolster our Clinical Leadership Team and further promote, strengthen and continuously improve excellence in nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Regional Head of Nursing / Regional Lead Practitioner, you will be a pinnacle member of our leadership and management team. Overseeing our nursing services across our Urgent Treatment Centres, providing support to our Director of Nursing and being a strong and visible clinical leader to our nurses and clinical teams. In this role you will manage a number of UTC Lead Practitioners; ensuring our services meet key performance indicators and that our patients will always receive a high quality and safe service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this varied role you will work closely with our Clinical &amp; Medical Directors along with operational managers to support with mobilisation and implementation of new services, ensure clinical governance policies are followed across sites and continuously strive to identify and implement opportunity to improve our service offering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full list of responsibilities can be found in the Job Description which you can downloadhere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be considered for this position you will be a first level registered nurse or paramedic, hold a recognised teaching and assessing qualification (or mentorship course), hold a masters degree (or equivalent) and be a practicing dual trained ANP / ENP / ECP(Minor Injuries and Minor Illnesses Course at Level 7) and experienced within an acute or primary care setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A competitive salary and generous benefits package is offered (including NHS pension) in addition to longer term career development opportunities available as Greenbrook Healthcare continue to grow and lead innovation within Urgent Care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Please do not hesitate to apply.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An informal discussion regarding the role with our Director of Nursing Matthew Parkes, is encouraged and advised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Interviews will be held in the week commencing Monday 23rd November 2020&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: Sunday 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to amend the closing date based upon the number of applications received. Vacancies attracting a high volume of applications may therefore close earlier than advertised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Greenbrook is an equal opportunities employer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Please note the following shortlisting approach will be applied:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;Round 1&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;- Any staff at risk of redundancy within the Totally plc group, who meet the essential criteria, will be considered in the first instance for this vacancy.&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;Round 2&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;- If the vacancy has not been filled after round 1, any employee Affected by Change within the Totally plc group, who meet the essential criteria, will be then be considered for this vacancy.&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;Round 3&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;- If the vacancy has not been filled after round 2, we will consider and shortlist all remaining applications in accordance with our recruitment policy.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (Exceptions Order) 1975 and as such it will be necessary for a submission for Disclosure to be made to the Disclosure and Barring Service (formerly known as CRB) to check for any previous criminal convictions.&lt;/p&gt;
